# Stage 3 test: 2D notched beam.
# A 100x50 mm rectangle with a midspan rectangular notch (8 mm wide, 25 mm
# tall — half-height, like a typical SENB specimen). Generator suppresses
# point placement strictly inside the notch box and seeds vertices on the
# notch boundary at finer spacing. Converter-side deletion comes with the
# 2D converter core (Stage 7).
#@output nodes.dat
#@domain 2
#@diam 0.004
#@maxiter 100000
#@perflag 2 0 0
#@ranint -1
#@ranflag 1
# bounding-box corners widen the localiser
#@vertex 1 coords 2 -0.005 -0.005 refine 1. radius 0.
#@vertex 2 coords 2  0.105  0.055 refine 1. radius 0.
#@controlvertex 1 coords 2 0.005 0.0
#@controlvertex 2 coords 2 0.095 0.0
#@controlvertex 3 coords 2 0.05  0.05
#@rect 1 box 4 0. 0. 0.10 0.05 refine 1.
#@notch 1 box 4 0.046 0.0 0.054 0.025 surfacerefine 0.5 edgerefine 0.5
